19 maij 1692
Londen Jan du maistre
depuis ma derniere de 8 cour receu la chere vre de 29 passe, cy joint facture de
8 pour la vallens il
vre pacqnette N.6 portant &
vous plaira me crediter, I have forwarded this day god send itt wel to you
hope to send you next weeck one order lase becing now best all the yeare
I have now acquantens, of anney deles in wheited browne trade att brnges,
my factor, or correspondent their is S raphael Coots I shall infarme of
him, to knoto dra who draiwe that trades advice you, no ship yett gon this
hier from antwerp to ostend, on londen de recteley, because vere libtle goods
excaveig goods coome ont to be sent that way & what compt itt send by
wagens yett the forst opportunitie that present shall sen them you
I have drawne this day on you £100 in my bill att 2 uso pay ableto the
order of m Jaques bofschaert att 33 „ 8 more then a pernine abore the cours
pray gill due honnour & be sure that I am in all occasions
Londen John Kent & comp
sence my last of 15 cur receaved yours of ditto & 29 past
as also advice, of the arrivall, of the amsterdam convoy from Hully
am nott a listle Barsllett startblet & concerned att itt, beinge att a
confusion that others shall have their goods, & I know nott what, you rott
leit mee posctisiles
mee, that N 28, 22, 23, 24 & 27 should be shipped foee amst
& sence & do nott know upon what accompt or opinion some are shipped
for rotterdam, I have jound you all a longe inclined for the rotterdam
hadt
ships & yett those of amsterdam have at frequenter & better convoyers
then thase of rotterdam, sure your freind att hull is concerned, or hath no good
corresponden ie, butt I doubt you have to much the do, & that you can
nott performe, all your commissions, there by you seem not inclined, to serve
mee in commission, and baetward in performinge my orders. I have send
you a patterne, of filk, nott to have a staine cullour butt a
mixt sture upon that ground, for a cullour not mixt is nott al all
demanded, nay attroad mixture the onley mode, so that a staine, or I meane
an even cullour nott mixt should be loft to the ceall: defire
phn le send med pattar when new clldins apleare, and
the Amsterdam convoy heengreaddy to coom frim
London, donbt not but you have shipped some wad
Ivonder you make no men hin of goods readd
for ostendi & the rest of my orders. I seee the ex is
yett afalling, so vermitt mee rnst yett
when you hae spanish cloths for holland,& that you should loose
the opportunitie, oft the convoye, forwant of dozens, so forward
the spanish cloths without dozms. wee have advice that Jan
bart of duynkerke gett att Dea, so that no small ffeare for the
rotterdam convoy, when I order goods in the nord, to be shipped for
Amsterdam & rotterdam, is nott to have al with one convoye, butt with
each sortimment, least, of anney misfortune I should nott be to
much to want of goods, now the amsterdam convoye beinge come hath brons
butt N. 108. 21, & 24 of the latter haveinge, no not bill of loading cydt
so what assortiment is that if the rotterdam convoy should ben last, &
my for balles of cloth, hath you shipped att leaft N. 23 & 23 far amst

22 maij
Amst geert ovaler Rover
t sedert mijnen van 19 deser den ue vanden selven ditto becommen godt laf
dat het hills convoy, costy behouden gearriveert is, doch is mij uytterlijck
leet die quaede directie tot hul int aflaeden der goederen, en dat op een bloot
gerucht sonder sekerheyt, aloft de convoyers, met descottte schepen sonder
die van hull soude syn vertrocken, ick ben voorlede iaer oock soo gevaren
ende daer door het ongeluck gehadt, met het rotterdams convoij b packen
voor 3 te verliesen, godt wille nu beter voyagie geven, is echter niet houder
aehterdencken alsoo sij maer een convoij schip hebben, ende ian lart insee is
Ick en twijfele niet, oft ue heeft de £ 200 laeten assureren d'expeditie van
de geurniveerde packen, is ue uytterlyck gerecomandeer t sijnde N. 108 met
peeter wjngaert, waer van nochtans de gadette geen mentie maeckt N.21
met thomas havorth, seker is N. 14 oock geloeden, doch hebbe daer
van geen sekerheyt als mede niet van N. 38, synde vanden selven inhout
en qualiteyt als N108, & N. 39 met 1½ witten bay van a 65 & 18
dosijntiens van 18 a weirt samen ƒ 500:- oft die non oock p costy
of rotter. sijn af gelaeden hebbe noch te vernemen soo ue deselve voorcome
gelieftn met alle eexpeditie voorts te helpen vernemende geirnewat
